Interface ContentDelegator

All Known Implementing Classes:
StringContentHandler
public interface ContentDelegator

Specifies the methods that must be implement to be a ContentDelegator for the UserAgent (ie a class that handles unsupported content-types or delegates them to the appropriate handler).

Since:
0.9.0
Author:
Tom Cervenka

              java.lang.String proxyHost,
              int proxyPort,

              java.lang.String contentType,
              java.io.BufferedReader br)
              throws java.lang.Exception
Processes the specified BufferedReader from the specified UserAgent, using the various context variables as required.

Parameters:
ua - the UserAgent, which provides the content to be processed in the form of the BufferedReader.
proxyHost - the ip address of http proxy or null for no proxy.
proxyPort - the port of http proxy, or 0 for no port.
urlStr - the url, which may include the querystring
userAgent - the browser identification string.
referer - the url of the current page.
cookieStr - is the value of the cookie header (eg "foo=val1; bar=val2").
authStr - is the value of the Authorization header for Basic Authentication (eg "Basic saer98yugsh98trshjy9sdyh") -- see http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2617.txt for more info.
contentType - the content type of the data supplied by the BufferedReader.
Throws:
java.lang.Exception
